0 Param data.1 string m_text: It just keeps getting louder.
Yeah.
Who were you talking to?
What does it matter?
Ha ha!
Answering a question with another question! Classic Kagachi! That's great!
What do you want?
Um, well...
Would you wanna—I dunno—go somewhere together? The next time we get a break?
Or I could cook us something—
Not really, no. Sorry.

I-It's fine! I kinda figured—it's fine!
Don't worry about it.
I'm fine!
Hey, you two—the Watch meeting is starting.
Y-Yeah, I knew that!
Actions that go against the laws of reincarnation will be met with severe consequence, as discussed.
Your first priority is to purge the black markets and seize the criminals dealing in illicit goods.
Even if we have to do it by force?
Naturally. Any who resist must be punished as well.
Um... Don't you think that would make people, you know, start to hate the Watchers?
Don't be ridiculous. Consider this an opportunity for redemption.
The recent scandals have caused the sovereign no small amount of grief.
Scandals?
How else would you describe it?
Watchers committing crimes, disturbing the peace—the list of sins is long.
And now the Fallen are wreaking more havoc than ever. That is due to your negligence, is it not?
You're crossing a line you really shouldn't.
What did you say to me?
Father—
Everyone knows to take the laws seriously.
We do all that we can do, even hardening our hearts to endure the horrors of death. Who could doubt our intentions?
We don't do it for you or your sovereign mother, or even for the realm.
Watchers are who we are because we are human above all else.
A commendable attitude, Kushi.
I can see your loyalty to each other runs deep.
Take care that your bonds don't become fetters that drag you all down together.
Ooh, I HATE that man!
Sorry, everyone. I didn't mean for things to get so intense.
I think it's best if we get on with doing what needs doing.
That said, if anyone feels our loyalty to the realm starts to waver, you bring it up so we can discuss it together. Yeah?
All right, let's get started.
Any business exploiting reincarnation for its own benefit needs to be shut down, but that doesn't mean we should resort to violence if we can help it.
Kujo, you handle the charm peddler.
What? I've even got one of her charms...
What was that?
Nothing!
Ioga, Wucan, you figure out how to get rid of those stubborn Ark of Hope bastards. They're still at it.
Got it!
And as for you two—I've got a different task in mind.
Which is?
More and more women keep disappearing.
I want you to find them.
I trust you understand what us looking for them means.
It means they might be dead.
Might, mind you. Might.
Kagachi, I want you to go after a man named Juta.
Who is he?
A suspect.
There's a witness who claims to have seen him meeting with the women who disappeared.
His house is to the southeast.
I'll head that way.
Mayura, you learn what you can from the Lost.
All right.
I'm counting on you.
What are you doing here?
One of the Lost was a child... A child! I'll never forgive this monster.
You better not kill our suspect.
Anyone home?
Good, you're—
Wait—you're not...
Who are you?
Watchers. We'd like to have a word.
Well, I wouldn't. Goodbye.
Strange. Something tells me we better stick around.
Yeah, I get the feeling he was expecting company. Let's wait and see who shows up.
Someone's here.
I can't hear a thing.
You sure like to keep me waiting, don't you?
Right, I've got to get going. I trust you can handle things without me.
What now?
Stay here and keep watch. I'll go after Juta.
He's only speaking to young women. Wonder what he's got to say...
Hey. What did that man say to you?
Huh?
He said he was looking for a maid. Asked if I'd be interested in working for him.
Oh?
Yeah, but I already have a job, so I said no. Why do you ask?
No reason.
He's got to be hiding something in that house. We should have a look while he's out.
Where the hell did Mayura get to?
No one's here. Maybe she left to tail that guy from before.
It's open.
I suppose I owe it to Kushi to investigate.
What is this place?
Necromancy?
There's more than enough here to prove his guilt.
There's someone here, Kagachi!
Who?
One of the Lost is in this room.
Who are you?
My name is Emilia.
I was Juta's wife.
Why haven't you moved on yet? Lingering affection for your husband?
I want to stop him.
From doing what?
My husband means to resurrect me. He'll stop at nothing...not even the theft of innocent life.
I see.
I'll stop him.
And I'll make sure he lets go of you, too.
There should be an entrance to the basement somewhere in the house.
Take me with you, and I'll lead you to his laboratory.
Deal.
Juta! Stop!
You... You're that Watcher from before!
How did you get in here?
Wh-Why have you come!?
I've been asked to save you.
"Save" me? I've already been saved!
By my research... It saved me, and it will save Emilia!
Kagachi... They're all here.
Who?
Angry souls. Vengeful souls. Sad souls... So many emotions, all flooding in.
They're saying...he did horrible things to them.
It hurts... Kagachi, my heart hurts so much...
I know. Hold on. I'll give them release.
Just how many lives did you take?
I didn't kill anyone! I only put what was given to me to good use!
It's awful...
The anger, the hate, the pain left in their wake. You don't feel it at all, do you?
Feel? Feel what? What is there to feel!? WHAT!?
Shut up... SHUT UP!
I'm doing this to bring Emilia back!
You'd do the same if you lost someone you loved!
Don't lie! You know you would!
You WOULD!
Wh-What? What's happening? What's that rumbling!?
What in the name of...!?
Nothing more than the shades of what they once were. They can't even be sent onward now.
Let me shoulder the burden of your suffering. Let me end it.
Juta's gone!
You will pay for your crimes.
No!
No! No! Get away from me!
D-Don't... Please, stop!
NOOOOOOOO!
Enough!
Your wife didn't want any of this.
Shut UP!
What do you know? Nothing!
You don't know anything...
Anything at all...
Aaah... Haahhh...
You're the one who knows nothing.
I pray that your beloved can still be reborn.
Aaahh...
AAAAAHHHHH! EMILIAAAAA!
Juta...
It's over.
Juta won't hold you here any longer.
I just wanted my wife back...
I wanted...
I wanted to see her again.
That's all...
Emilia...
I love you, Juta.
I will always love you. Even in my next life.
Are you all right with this?
Will you be able to let go and move on if he's still alive?
I believe he's taken the first step on a better path.
I think so, too.
Thank you. I think I can pass on my own now.
Right.
Thank you.
Nice work, Kagachi.
But where did Mayura get to?
She ended up following another lead. I haven't seen her since.
It's possible she's back at Juta's place.
She knows better than to not report in.
If you see her, tell her she needs to come make her report. In the meantime, I need to check on something.
Understood.
Oh! Hey, Kagachi!
We're supposed to seize all the equipment that guy was hiding. Lord Leo's orders. I came to help!
Have you seen Mayura?
Mayura?
Um, nope!
Right.
Kagachi...
Mayura?
What's up with you? Talking to yourself?
I thought I heard something, too.
It sounded close.
It reeks in here. What is this place?
Hellooo? Anyone there?
Yeah, I am.
What is this? A secret lair?
Look at this place...
It's a morgue. These must be all the people he kidnapped for his experiments.
They need to be identified, right?
Let me help.
Stay back!
What is it?
Just...just stay back.
You don't want to see this...
What are you...
No!
One of our own. A Watcher. How...
Mayura...
Say...something...
Please...
Do not shame the Watchers any further.
Right... Today's the day of the Seven-Day Sending. I'd forgotten.
The day the people send their prayers to the Beyond.
It's almost like they're all helping to send her off.
I hope she can hear them.
She's not the type to stick around, but I don't doubt she's got one or two regrets.
After all, she was nothing if not a perfectionist.
Considering this'd be my last chance, part of me wanted to be selfish and go ask her...
But if she does have any regrets, I don't think I'm the one she'd wanna tell. If anything, she'd want to speak to you.
Would you go to Kiro Marsh in my stead?
She really loved that place.
Maybe she's still there.
Please, Kagachi...
Mayura.
Kagachi...
I'm such a failure.
You'd think a Watcher would know better than to let herself have regrets, yet have them I do.
And after I spent my whole life preaching against the very concept to anyone I ever met...
It's shameful.
You're being too hard on yourself.
You're being too hard on yourself.
Oh, please. That isn't like the Kagachi I know.
All out of your usual level stares and stoicism, huh?
But really... Thank you. It helped.
Nothing to say to that, hm? It'd be nice if you could cut me some slack just this once, considering...
I... Never mind. I'm sorry.
Is there anything I can do?
You've already done everything you can—
—just coming here to see me.
If you say so.
This place was my favorite, you know.
Yeah. I heard.
I...I'm really dead, aren't I?
I never thought this would happen.
Growing old always seemed like a given to me.
I was so sure that I'd live a long life.
Knowing that I'll never see my dad again hurts...
Knowing that I'll never see you again makes me want to cry...
This...
This isn't FAIR!
I don't... I don't want to go! I don't wanna...
Embrace Mayura.
Stare at Mayura.
You're so warm.
You being so kind now, at the end... It almost makes it worse...
*sigh*
I think I feel a little better now.
Sorry...
I guess this is it... Sorry I couldn't get those memories back for you...
Don't worry about it.
Kagachi, can I ask you one last favor?
Sure.
If you can...will you look for Izana's memories?
I will.
Thank you.
Oh...
And tell Kujo I'm sorry.
Do you think she'll understand what for?
It's time to say goodbye now.
I'll see you again when I'm reborn. I know I will.
I know...
Sorry I made you do that... But I didn't think I'd be able to play the stoic Watcher if I'd gone to see her.
She'll be all right. She left smiling.
That's good...
I, um...came to see Mayura off.
I appreciate it.
Poor Mayura...
If she would've just stayed put like you told her...
I tried to stop her, but she wouldn't listen.
Wait—you were there?
Huh? Oh, um, yeah.
Once I heard where the suspect's house was, I went right over.
How did you know?
Heard from who?
How did you know?
What? Someone must have mentioned it. Right?
Heard from who?
Huh? I thought Kushi mentioned it, didn't he?
I'm the only one who knew.
And Mayura said one of the Lost told her.
Right! That was it! A Lost Soul told me, too!
What? What is UP with you?
Nothing's up with me.
You're the one acting funny.
Maybe because my best friend just died!
But I guess you never considered how I felt! Mayura's DEAD and she's STILL all you can think about!
Why did you let Mayura go in by herself?
Or maybe I should be asking—
—if you did go with her, why she was the only one who got killed.
AAAAARRRRGGGHHHHHHHH!
I—can't—take it—anymore!
I hate her... I HATE HER!
You know, don't you? DON'T YOU? You know everything!
You know exactly what I did!
Mayura told you, didn't she? I know she did, that two-faced Daemon!
She asked me to tell you something.
So tell me!
She said to tell you she was sorry.
She... What?
AAAARRGHHHH! What does that mean? What do I do!?
No—nonono!
I'm sorry... I'm so...
I'm so sorry...
It was you, wasn't it? I didn't want to believe you were capable...
You killed all those women and gave their corpses to Juta.
I'm...not exactly pretty, obviously... All my life, it felt like I was the butt of someone's sick joke.
Everyone else was so beautiful, so why... Why was I the only one...
I never thought anyone would look twice at me...
I hated myself... So much...
I just wanted to disappear.
And then I saw him kill someone... It was so awful, but I...I laughed...
Is that when you became his accomplice?
That was you at Juta's house. You killed Mayura.
Death can't be taken back.
If you want to put things right, you don't get to wait for your next life. You have to start with the one you have now.
I'm sorry... I'm so sorry...
Kagachi, do you feel that?
He's coming!
I'm...sorry...
Kagachi... I...really...
The truth is...
That...that was the Night Devil.
You know him?
There was no one who didn't. But, that was before you were born.
A murderous phantom that appeared out of thin air and disappeared without a trace.
They called him the Executioner then.
The family of one of his victims put an end to him.
And then he turned into this mythical figure. A legend everyone knows, but knows nothing about.
Now that he's claimed victims, the kingdom has no choice but to act.
He'll try to kill again. And as a Watcher, I'll be there to stop him when he does.
How do you plan on doing that, exactly?
Honestly, I don't know.
But he'll keep getting away if we do nothing.
I need to learn more about him.
You aren't thinking—
Zale. It may be grasping at straws, but it's better than just waiting around.
I think I'll go pay him a visit in the dungeons.
All right. I'll inform Lord Leo.
Be careful.
Say goodbye to Kujo for me.
I will.
